rComments: Would seriously avoid taking his section of macroeconmics. His grading is opaque - he asks for concision, but fails you unless you word vomit everything you know about a topic, doesn't give full marks on tests, sets questions relating to readings that haven't been assigned. Seems to dislike teaching this class.

The worst class I have ever taken. Corak is a subjective grader and is unable to tell you why you lost points from an assignment or test. Assignments are ridiculously long, exams are tedious (get prepared to memorize the stats Can website), and the marking is unfair. Take ANY other professor for macro - this course will cause unnecessary stress.

This class was not at all enjoyable for the simple reason that students found the grading overly harsh and sometimes arbitrary. Perhaps Prof Corak feels that being a difficult grader will inspire his students to study harder. It does not have this effectit is demoralizing.
